title: For Sale:  NFA Class III Gun Trust, (additional Estate Planning Package, see inside)
postcontent:
If you are not trading then you have to pay through gunbroker.com so I can get the reviews. The price is low because I want the reviews.	

If you live in Central Florida, we can talk about possibly meeting up face to face for a consultation out at a coffee shop or at my office(different address from the one listed below). Feel free to call ahead of time to ask questions. I'm only selling NFA Trusts through gunbroker at this time, so I can get the reviews. The reviews are worth more to me in the end. That's the why the price is good, and the additional deals are better. In Florida, Private ownership of Class III firearms and items requires the local chief of police or sheriff's signature, fingerprints and photos. When you are not around, and if you don't know the laws behind proper storage, you possibly leave your loved ones with constructive possession issues. Also the local chief of police or sheriff is not required to provide their signature and they may deny you your right to own Class III items by simply "losing" the paperwork. With a proper Trust, that is avoided. Also my Trusts can be used in conjunction with a wide array of other estate planning documents. The NFA Trust in actuality is initially(can be modified as you wish before execution) a Revocable Living Trust with NFA friendly provisions that properly deal with the transfer(purchase), storage, and possible future transfers in relation to the acquired Class III items. An LLC requires annual fees and state filings or the LLC defaults leaving both you and your loved ones in possession of a restricted item. A Trust allows for people other than yourself(acting as Trustees) to use and enjoy the firearms as part of their duties in ensuring their proper protection, function, maintenance, and value. A trust is a BATFE approved method of Class III item ownership that protects you, protects your friends and family from constructive possession issues and gives you the control over when and where your items will be transferred after your death. Who will inherit them, who can inherit them, and if you would like, for the Trust to keep going on after your death so that your inheritors are still protected by the Trust. Generic and fill-in-the-blank asset or estate trusts from the internet or your buddy down the street who is not a lawyer, are not good enough. It may be enough for the application, but it might not be good enough should BATFE ever have a reason to look closer. Do it right the first time with a Trust that not only protects your Class III items, but can also protect your other assets. My Trusts are not slapped together Trusts, I can only finish them after I have spoken to you personally and consulted you about your needs, they are painstakingly assembled to work with Florida's laws and the NFA. The Trust can be used later in the future to acquire more Class III items as well, or as a larger part of your estate planning needs and desires. For a total of $400 you can also get the Trust and: Simple Will: for dispensation of personal effects and determination of burial. Not for the dispensation of your house. May be used to determine you takes your cars when you pass. Memorandum of Trust: necessary for creating bank accounts in the name of the Trust. Pour-Over Last Will & Testament: for having what assets you have not put in the Trust, added to the Trust. Also for having the proceeds from life insurance policies go to the Trust. Also I can prepare and mail letters to your life insurance carrier so that they put your Trust down as the beneficiary. General Durable Power of Attorney: typically for when or if you become legally or medically incapacitated. Specific Durable Limited Power of Attorney: can be used to take care of specific measures like selling or buying a car or house. Appointment of Healthcare Surrogate Alternative Appointment of Healtchare Surrogate Codicil/Amendments: for when you may want to add things to your Will such as personal possessions. Living Will: to have your desires be known in case you become afflicted so as to be in a vegetative state. I.E. be kept on life support, have the feeding tube remain in place, or prevent heroic medical measures. Pet Trust: In the State of Florida it is no recognized how one can create a Trust for the care of their pets should they pass. David Koberlein, Esq. David Koberlein, P.A. Florida Bar ID 89817 REDACTED 61 Seminola Blvd, Casselberry Florida, 32707

title: For Sale:  Slide Fire Solutions SSAR-15
postcontent:
Factory New 

Right Hand Stock 

Slide Fire Solutions' ground breaking "Slide Stock" technology and ergonomic design provide the ability to Slide Fire safely, offering a new element of entertainment for recreational shooters everywhere! 

Applying principles that have been used for over 40 years to bump fire, the SSAR-15's radical design enables the shooter to fire and AR-15 as quickly as desired without compromising their own safety or the safety of others around them. Unlike traditional bump firing. The SSAR-15 allows the shooter to properly hold their firearm and maintain complete control at all times. In addition, as a result of the forward movement required to discharge each round, the shooter naturally corrects their point-of-aim for each shot and prevents recoil from pushing the firearm's muzzle upward in an unsafe direction. 

In principal the SSAR-15 functions similar to the Gatlin system. When operating a Gatlin system the shooter operates a crank in a circular motion to activate the firing mechanism. Every 1/5 rotation of the crank will discharge a round. The shooter will then continue forward another 1/5 of a rotation to fire the next round, and so on. With the SSAR-15 the shooter activates the firing mechanism by moving the upper assembly forward to discharge a round. To discharge the next round the operator must again move the upper assembly forward. As with the Gatlin system, an AR-15 equipped with the SSAR-15 will never fire automatically. 

MADE IN THE USA

Right Hand Configuration

Constructed of Premium Reinforced High Strength Polymer

Compatible with Mil-Spec and Commercial Buffer Tubes

Winter Trigger Guards and some Sling Plates may not be compatible. 
INCLUDES: SSAR-15, Interface Block, Hex Key, Instructions and BATFE Approval Letter.
 I bought this for a family member, and he has not come up with the funds to buy  it. So here it is no tax, no shipping $350

title: For Sale/Trade:  Lee-Enfield No. 4 Mk. I/II 1943/1945 PRICE DROP
postcontent:
This is a great condition Lee-Enfield No. 4 Mk. I/II (which means it was reissued in 1945 with Mk. II specs) originally made in 1943. This rifle was made in BSA in Birmingham, England  and is in great condition. Since BSA did not make as many rifles  and are not as common as a Savage or a Longbranch, that makes this rifle that much more rare and more collectable. I have taken this rifle apart many times to clean it (as I do religiously) and there is no pitting or rust to be found. However, there is an import mark at the end of the barrel that link it to Vermont (?). This rifle is in great condition and has great rifling and a dark, but very clean, bore. Also has flip micrometer/300yrd Battle sight.

Keep in mind, this is valued at around $350+ considering the manufacturer. MAKE ME AN ACCEPTABLE OFFER. Only offer me what you would be happy giving. I am open to trades plus cash on either end depending on what is offered.

Technical  Specifications

Model - MKA 1919
Operation - Gas operated Semi-auto Shotgun
Caliber - 12 gauge
Range - 35 mt.The Akdal MKA 1919 is a gas operated, semi-automatic shotgun manufactured in Turkey by Ucyildiz Arms*.  The MKA 1919 not only resembles the M16 rifle but the control and function are similar.  The MKA 1919 is unlike any other 12 gauge shotgun in the U.S. as it is very light, ergonomic, and magazine fed.

The MKA 1919 semi-automatic shotgun uses a conventional gas-operated action which is located around the support tube that runs below the barrel.  The return spring is also located around the same support tube which is concealed by an enlarged polymer handguard.  The MKA 1919 barrel can be very easily removed from the upper receiver.   The upper receiver is manufactured from an aluminum alloy while the lower receiver, pistol grip, and stock are manufactured as one piece from impact resistant polymer.
The MKA 1919 comes with two 5-round metal detachable magazines and 3 internal chokes.  The magazine release button mimics the M16 rifle location.  The manual safety also duplicates the M16 style being located on the left side of the receiver above the pistol grip.  The top of the receiver has a carrying handle and  integral picatinny rail for mounting rear sights, or any optical accessories.  The MKA 1919 12 gauge shotgun is appropriate for all levels of hunting and sporting enthusiasts.  It comes in Black and "BONZ" camo versions and is reasonably priced for our distributors and customers alike.  

Weight (Empty) - 6 1/2 lbs 
Barrel Length - 47 cm.
Magazine Capacity - 5 Round
Safety - Manuel safety lever
Overall Length - 96,40 cm.
Mobile shock - 5 cm — 10 cm — 15 cm
